Lesson 9: Sentence Structure I

Sentence structure 1:
A は B です - "A is B"
A は B じゃないです - "A is not B" (More colloquial)
A は B ではありません - "A is not B" (More formal)
This is used to describe the state of something. 

Sentence structure 2: 
~ませんか
This is used to extend an invitation. Note that the negative of the verb must be used. 
